'''伊卡黑石'''（Ica Stones），又稱'''伊卡石頭'''、'''伊卡石'''，是[[祕魯|祕魯]][[伊卡大區|伊卡大區]]的[[安山岩|安山岩]]民俗工藝品，刻有各種藝術圖案賣到外國，後來引發科學騙局而大受觀光客歡迎<ref name="Skepdic">{{cite book|author=Carroll, Robert P.|title=The skeptic's dictionary: a collection of strange beliefs, amusing deceptions, and dangerous delusions|publisher=Wiley|location=New York|year=2003|pages=169–71|isbn=0-471-27242-6|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=6FPqDFx40vYC&pg=PA169|access-date=2011-11-23|archive-date=2020-12-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210160753/https://books.google.com/books?id=6FPqDFx40vYC&pg=PA169}}</ref><ref name="Fortean">{{cite journal|title=Jurassic library - The Ica Stones|url=http://www.forteantimes.com/features/articles/259/jurassic_library_the_ica_stones.html|last=Coppens|first=P|date=October 2001|journal=[[Fortean_Times|Fortean Times]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080827173630/http://forteantimes.com/features/articles/259/jurassic_library_the_ica_stones.html|archivedate=2008-08-27|deadurl=yes|access-date=2011-11-23}} Available without registration at [http://www.philipcoppens.com/jurassiclibrary.html philipcoppens.com] {{Wayback|url=http://www.philipcoppens.com/jurassiclibrary.html|date=20111104024312}}</ref>。   

1966年祕魯人Javier Cabrera建立一個博物館收集超過一萬顆伊卡黑石商品，雕刻主題有恐龍、星空圖、世界地圖、巨人與恐龍互鬥。他出書《伊卡黑石篆函》（The Message of the Engraved Stones of Ica）宣稱這些石頭是與恐龍時代共存的人類所作，並透過[[搞笑諾貝爾獎|搞笑諾貝爾獎]]得主[[艾利希·馮·丹尼肯|艾利希·馮·丹尼肯]]大肆宣傳。1973年製作者Basilio Uschuya承認是為提高銷量而編的騙局，說：「刻這些石頭比耕田輕鬆。」至今當地民俗藝術家依舊製作上述題材的伊卡黑石賣給觀光客當[[伴手禮|伴手禮]]<ref>{{cite book|title=The Message of the Stones|last=Cabrera|first=Javier|location=Ica, Peru|url=http://members.cox.net/icastones/02a-book-chapter-1.htm|accessdate=12-05-10|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111202175320/http://members.cox.net/icastones/02a-book-chapter-1.htm|archivedate=2011-12-02}}</ref>。

